            "id": "73cca155562e462185327",
            "questionText": "An isolated community is installing a new solar farm that generates an average power of $!$200\\,\\mathrm{kW}$!$ for $!$8$!$ hours per day. During this time, a total of $!$5.76 \\times 10^6\\,\\mathrm{C}$!$ of charge is transferred. Calculate the voltage gain $!$V$!$ created by the solar farm.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "6857a8e3851b4b2babab1",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the formula that relates electrical power to energy and time. Which of the following formulas represents this relationship?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "64f6d809-190a-42c7-8bc9-a4f4eceaee29",
                        "b866d70e-adbe-4435-be21-c2c36ea664ca"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$P = \\frac{\\Delta E}{\\Delta t}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$P = \\Delta E \\times \\Delta t$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\Delta E = P + \\Delta t$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "ba74a7a7a48f4595adee3",
                    "stepText": "Great! Now, the power is given in kilowatts and the time is given in hours. Convert the time from hours to seconds to continue with the energy calculation. What is the value in seconds for 8 hours?",
